  "texts": [
    "The definition of the covering map given above, based on the data {x i, w i, z i }, is an overconstrained system [6,7].",
    "The complex dimension of the space of possible covering maps for the n-punctured genus g Riemann surface Σ g,n based off the data {x i, w i, z i } is 3 -3g -n. This is generically negative and so a covering map need not exist.",
    "However, we notice that this isdim(M g,n) and so one would expect that an integral over -25 -JHEP04(2024)048 moduli space will increase this dimension back to zero, giving rise to a discrete set of covering maps.",
    "This makes intuitive sense in the context of string theory correlators: consider the genus g = 0 case, whilst {x i, w i: i = 1,..., n} and {z i: i = 1, 2, 3} are physical, the remaining z i are not physical as they break diffeomorphism invariance.",
    "The significance of this is that our localisation in section 4.3 will include a sum over the discrete set of possible covering maps."
  ],
